Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.44,0:00:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school life, they say, is rosy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.32,0:00:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And rosy, they say, is high school life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.36,0:00:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school life is always\Ntreated as being rosy,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.61,0:00:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so much so, that being told\Nas much is commonplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.62,0:00:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, I don't think that all\Nhigh-schoolers want it to be rosy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.38,0:00:27.67,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,History Club
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.38,0:00:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take studying,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.71,0:00:29.04,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Boys Basketball Club
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.71,0:00:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and sports,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.04,0:00:30.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Ballroom Dancing Club
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.04,0:00:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and romantic affairs... there are\Npeople who show no interest in any of them, aren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.34,0:00:32.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hocus-Pocus Club
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.22,0:00:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are students who prefer things\N"gray," as it were, aren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.14,0:00:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess that might be\Na pretty empty life, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.19,0:00:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, I never knew you had\Na masochistic streak.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.36,0:00:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Masochistic?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.07,0:00:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taking a negative view of studying,\Nsports, and romance...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.36,0:00:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The perennially gray person.\NThat's who you are, Hotaro, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.45,0:00:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I have a\Nnegative view of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.70,0:01:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not in {\i1}your {\i0}opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.33,0:01:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Energy-conserving...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.41,0:01:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you are, right, Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.54,0:01:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're simply not interested in anything\Nyou consider to be a hassle or frivolous.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.34,0:01:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which brings us to your motto...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.34,0:01:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If I don't have to do\Nsomething, I don't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.72,0:01:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I have to do something,\NI do it quickly."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.60,0:01:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. But you know, Hotaro,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.56,0:01:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you, having not joined\Nany of the clubs offered
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.64,0:01:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in this shrine of various clubs\Nknown as Kamiyama High School,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.94,0:01:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you've ended up being\Nthe color gray itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.73,0:01:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That "empty life," as you call it,\Nis nothing other than masochism.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.15,0:01:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure do like to run your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.11,0:01:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now {\i0}you're telling me? You've known\Nme since middle school, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph, whatever. You can leave without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.83,0:01:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without you? What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.08,0:01:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that...? No, it couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.96,0:01:52.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Club Application
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.96,0:01:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A club application?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.71,0:01:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, you're joining a club?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.67,0:01:55.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Classic Literature
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.67,0:01:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Classic Lit Club, at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.42,0:01:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're familiar with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.30,0:02:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I am! But, Hotaro,\Nwhat possessed you to get into classic lit?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.85,0:02:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's... a letter from your sister, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.31,0:02:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She mailed it from India.\NVanarasi, or someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see the problem now. It was\Na request from your sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.78,0:02:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, it's on the verge of\Nbeing shut down for lack of members.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.44,0:02:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She wants me to join so it can keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember, your sister's thing was...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.41,0:02:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aikido and takedown moves. If she wants\Nto hurt you, she can really hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.29,0:02:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't turn this down, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.75,0:02:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, when she writes that there's\Nnothing I really want to do, she's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.29,0:02:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have any members\Nin the club, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.96,0:02:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.13,0:02:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you have the Classic Lit Club's\Nroom to yourself, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.30,0:02:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having your own private space\Ninside the school is a pretty nice thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.35,0:02:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Private space?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.68,0:02:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kami High!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.31,0:02:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I salute those who live an\Nenergy-consuming lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.98,0:02:49.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Faculty Office
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People often get the wrong idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.31,0:02:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's not as if I hold energy\Nconservation to be superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.78,0:03:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't look down on those\Nwho are more active.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.66,0:03:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just faithful to my own motto.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If I don't have to do\Nsomething, I don't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.45,0:03:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I have to do something,\NI do it quickly."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:12.62,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.42,0:03:12.62,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.62,0:03:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.83,0:03:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.84,0:03:23.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.55,0:03:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fourth floor of the auxiliary building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.18,0:03:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's as remote as it gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.95,0:04:29.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:37.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away the\Nawkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.67,0:04:45.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.55,0:04:50.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.97,0:04:56.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.35,0:05:01.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.86,0:05:06.95,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.41,0:05:13.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.79,0:05:21.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.21,0:05:26.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.80,0:05:33.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.06,0:05:40.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.48,0:05:48.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.62,0:05:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.50,0:05:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the Classic Lit Club, too, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.50,0:06:00.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Return of the Time-Honored Classic Lit Club
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.38,0:06:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.42,0:06:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda. Chitanda Eru.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I have no idea who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Oreki Hotaro-{\i1}san{\i0}, right?\NFrom Class 1-B?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in Class 1-A.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.19,0:06:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, that doesn't really help much...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.69,0:06:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Class A? Then one of the elective classes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't happen to be\Nin my music class, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.57,0:06:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.36,0:06:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've only had that class once so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of memory does she have?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, so, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.58,0:06:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.58,0:06:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've joined the Classic Lit Club too,\Nso I came to pay my respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've joined the Classic Lit Club...\NI've joined the Classic Lit Club...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.76,0:06:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Classic Lit Club? Why would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.56,0:07:00.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have some personal reasons.\NWhat about you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.94,0:07:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, as long as there are\Nother members, that's terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.40,0:07:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rejoice, Sis. The Classic\NLit Club lives on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.57,0:07:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.95,0:07:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're leaving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.61,0:07:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Good luck. And\Ncould you lock up, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.04,0:07:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't lock up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.83,0:07:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.62,0:07:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a key.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.46,0:07:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.00,0:07:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.17,0:07:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you have one, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.55,0:07:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why{\i0}? You can't get into a locked\Nclassroom without a key, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.05,0:07:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, how the\Nhell did... Oh, excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, how did you\Nget into the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.31,0:07:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The door wasn't locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I got here, it was closed, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.73,0:07:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was closed? You mean, the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.32,0:07:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.44,0:07:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, are you saying that\NI was locked inside here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.95,0:07:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who locked it,\Nright? From the inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.74,0:07:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:08:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm the one with the key.\NWho else but you could have locked it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, is that a friend of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.25,0:08:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.13,0:08:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.46,0:08:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, sorry, sorry! I wasn't\Nintending to eavesdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.47,0:08:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't {\i1}intending {\i0}to, you {\i1}were{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.47,0:08:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be that as it may,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.09,0:08:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I see my hard-boiled Hotaro at a classroom\Nwindow alone with a girl, with evening closing in,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.93,0:08:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's only natural that\NI'd be a little curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.52,0:08:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean to interrupt your\Nlittle after-school rendezvous,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I've never been a Peeping Tom\Nbefore, so... U-Um... Um, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.03,0:08:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.57,0:08:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not. I'm joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.57,0:08:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.95,0:08:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that. That's just\Nthe sort of guy he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.62,0:08:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nothing beats an impromptu joke.\NIt creates a breeding ground for lies."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.62,0:08:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my motto.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.37,0:08:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.75,0:08:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Fukube Satoshi,\Nwould-be sophisticate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.50,0:08:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would-be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.26,0:08:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Smooth! Nice introduction, Hotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.05,0:08:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.55,0:08:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda Eru.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:09:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ch-Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}?! By Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0},\Ndo you mean, {\i1}the {\i0}Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.77,0:09:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.14,0:09:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, haven't you ever heard\Nof the Chitanda family?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.94,0:09:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are more than a few pedigreed,\Nprestigious families in Kamiyama,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.77,0:09:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you mention the "Four Higher\NPower Families," they're notable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's the Jumonji family of Arekusu Shrine,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:20.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Jumonji Family, Sarusuberi Family, Chitanda Family, Manninbashi\NFamily
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the bookstore tycoon Sasusuberi family,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the wealthy farmers of the Chitanda family,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.91,0:09:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the Manninbashi family,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.03,0:09:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who own the mountain timberlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each family name is one power\Nof ten greater than the last,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.08,0:09:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which is why people call them the\N"Four Higher Power Families."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.66,0:09:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.92,0:09:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if we're a\N"prestigious" family,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.96,0:09:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but that's the first time\NI've heard us be called that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.71,0:09:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You made that up, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.01,0:09:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, I'd like to be\Nthe one who coins terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.67,0:09:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they really do go\Nin orders of ten, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.26,0:09:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't act impressed; you'll swell his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.97,0:09:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, the oldest Chitanda girl is\Nknown for her high marks and fair features,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.85,0:09:47.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and for being a well-refined beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.44,0:09:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In middle school, she got high grades\Nin the prefectural practice exams,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.11,0:09:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I've seen her name around a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.98,0:09:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-ho, you're all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.69,0:09:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fluke. I just have\Na knack for taking tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:09:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I beg your pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.95,0:10:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, I heard all\Nabout it. Truly fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.62,0:10:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The way Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}got\Nlocked inside this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.75,0:10:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.25,0:10:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I came here, the door\Nto the room was unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.71,0:10:13.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlocked
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.71,0:10:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when Oreki-{\i1}san {\i0}arrived afterward,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.76,0:10:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he said the door was locked.\NIt's a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.13,0:10:18.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Locked
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.84,0:10:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you figure? You just\Nforgot that you locked it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.22,0:10:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. Kami High's doors are set up
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.93,0:10:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that you can only lock them\Nwith a key, both inside or outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.77,0:10:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that it is impossible for\NChitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}to have locked it from inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.61,0:10:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As big a know-it-all as ever, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.48,0:10:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd prefer you call me a database.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.44,0:10:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. Well, the lock business\Nmust have been some kind of mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.32,0:10:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.03,0:10:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.29,0:10:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.16,0:10:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.29,0:10:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did I get locked in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.17,0:10:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if it happens that I wasn't locked in,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.25,0:10:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how was it that I was able to\Nget inside this classroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.17,0:11:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposing that it was some kind of mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whose mistake was it,\Nand how was it made?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.72,0:11:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you think about it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.39,0:11:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.48,0:11:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.53,0:11:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... Okay. That is interesting.\NLet me think about it for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.20,0:11:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!\NOreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, do you have any thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.21,0:11:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, give him a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.79,0:11:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just a database, so I can't\Ncome up with any conclusions,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.88,0:11:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but not Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.34,0:11:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once he starts thinking,\Nhis reasoning is sound, in its own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.89,0:11:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put a sock in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:11:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.14,0:11:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... When did you enter the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.81,0:11:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was about three\Nminutes before you got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.73,0:11:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm. Did you notice anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.11,0:11:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.44,0:12:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something has been rattling around\Nunderfoot for a little while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.45,0:12:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I don't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.66,0:12:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can hear it. Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.37,0:12:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}, you have sharp ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.29,0:12:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.54,0:12:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Figured anything out yet, Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.25,0:12:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe. It's probably playing out\Nagain on the floor just below us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.19,0:12:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There. All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.53,0:12:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha. Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}must have gone\Nin the Earth Science prep room
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while that work was being done,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and was unlucky enough\Nto be locked inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.95,0:12:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have the circulating key.\NThere are also the master keys,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.33,0:12:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but students aren't allowed to use those.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how you knew it was the janitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.00,0:12:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, way to realize something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.88,0:13:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. So, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nwhat I don't understand is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why you didn't notice the sound of the lock\Nwhile you were inside the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.39,0:13:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, in that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.44,0:13:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking at that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.60,0:13:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's old, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.60,0:13:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.27,0:13:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.52,0:13:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, exceptionally so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.65,0:13:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.90,0:13:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, I still haven't\Npaid my respects yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your respects?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.41,0:13:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.53,0:13:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We {\i1}are {\i0}going to be together\Nin the Classic Lit Club, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.79,0:13:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Together?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.62,0:13:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fukube-{\i1}san{\i0}, what do you say\Nabout the Classic Lit Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.58,0:13:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not? Today has been interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.67,0:13:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to juggle it with Executive\NCommittee and Handicrafts Club, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.09,0:13:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, I'll join.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.18,0:13:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so will Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already filled out the application.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Yeah, well, the thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.93,0:13:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.57,0:14:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.11,0:14:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I've got it. I'm looking\Nforward to this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.91,0:14:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As am I. You, too, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.04,0:14:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, we have to choose a\Nclub president. What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.71,0:14:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good question. Hotaro isn't cut out\Nfor that sort of thing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.75,0:14:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, are you satisfied now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time-honored Classic Lit Club is back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.38,0:14:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And farewell to my days of peace\Nand energy conservation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.51,0:14:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I'm not saying goodbye yet.\NI'm not giving up on my peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.64,0:14:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will devote all of my efforts\Ntoward conserving energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.64,0:14:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.15,0:14:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and such a sharp mind, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.48,0:14:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This little lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:51.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seimei {\i0}('The Clearing')\NWhen all of nature is bright and clear,\Nand we see what grasses have sprouted
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.11,0:14:51.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.28,0:14:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It happened yesterday after school.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.41,0:14:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A 1st-year girl went to the\Nfourth floor of the auxiliary building.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.66,0:15:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As she did, she heard the beautiful melody of\N"Moonlight Sonata" coming from the music room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.38,0:15:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The setting sun bathed the\Nschool building in crimson.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.29,0:15:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The beautiful tones of...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Objection. It was raining yesterday,\Nand you couldn't see the setting sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was in the dampness\Nof the falling rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.26,0:15:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and evening's gloom was drawing near.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.89,0:15:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A sense of discomfort clung at her skin,\Naccompanied by the noise of the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.43,0:15:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's so not what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.23,0:15:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lured by the tones,\Nshe entered the music room,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.48,0:15:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when immediately, things fell silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lid of the piano was up,\Nbut there was no pianist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.77,0:15:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The curtains were drawn closed,\Nand the room was dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.90,0:15:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when she saw her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.74,0:15:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A girl student with long,\Nunkempt hair hanging over her face,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whose body was limp and slumped over,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.04,0:15:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and whose eyes were a fiery bloodshot red,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.33,0:15:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was staring at her from off to the side!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.25,0:15:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, once, here at Kamiyama High School,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.96,0:15:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was a Piano Club member who met a bitter\Naccidental death just before a national competition!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.63,0:15:51.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.59,0:15:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Who can say? Maybe there\Nwas one, but I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.26,0:15:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.10,0:15:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to admit, I didn't expect this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.10,0:16:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you, forgetting your\Nhomework and having to stay after?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.81,0:16:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did do it, yesterday.\NI just forgot to bring it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.94,0:16:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now, I have to sit here\Nwriting the same essay
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.74,0:16:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while listening to all your blather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.45,0:16:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.20,0:16:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, I hear there really\Nwas a disheveled-hair ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.66,0:16:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the talk of Class A\Nduring lunch break today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.41,0:16:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The important question is how\Nthis story is going to spread now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.42,0:16:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is one of the Seven Wonders of\NKamiyama High School... number two!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm waiting to see how many days\Nit takes to reach my own Class D.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.80,0:16:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm? Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.43,0:16:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When, where, and from whom\Ndid you hear this story?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.76,0:16:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier, in the club\Nroom, from Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.10,0:16:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is the second of the Seven Wonders,\Nthere's a first, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.48,0:16:48.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you tell me what that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.62,0:17:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}here {\i0}is where the two of you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.12,0:17:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wrote it up, Fukube-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.75,0:17:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, thank you. Sorry about that.\NAs an Executive Committee member,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.25,0:17:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to ask for these kinds of\Ntedious procedures to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.34,0:17:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. I {\i1}have {\i0}taken on\Nthe club presidency, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.09,0:17:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!\NYou came just at the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.47,0:17:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just heard an odd tale from Satoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.72,0:17:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, about that! At lunch today...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a story about the\N"Secret Club Recruitment Note."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.35,0:17:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.44,0:17:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Secret club?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.15,0:17:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, fill her in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.03,0:17:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Mm-hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.86,0:17:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, would you like to hear\Nthe tale of the "Secret Club"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.70,0:17:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.16,0:17:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a story I heard during\NExecutive Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.62,0:17:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you know, Kamiyama\NHigh School has many clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.50,0:17:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So naturally, there are a lot of\Nrecruitment posters for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.79,0:17:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the bulletin boards around the\Nschool get buried under these posters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.25,0:17:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the Executive Committee finds\Nan unauthorized poster or note,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they take them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.84,0:17:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:18:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, apparently, there's one\Nrecruitment note that turns up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.22,0:18:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for a club that nobody\Nknows anything about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.68,0:18:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last year, there was a meeting\Nplace and time written down
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.89,0:18:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on what looked like a scrap\Nof notebook paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.19,0:18:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that there's a secret club\Nthat not even the Committee knows about,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.48,0:18:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they are secretly recruiting members.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.40,0:18:16.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Diligent application and unswerving determination
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.98,0:18:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The club's objectives and membership is unknown,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but they do actually exist.\NTheir name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.20,0:18:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their name is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.66,0:18:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Joro Spider Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.58,0:18:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Joro Spider...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last year, Executive Committee\NChair Tanabe-{\i1}senpai{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.33,0:18:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,tried to contact the Joro Spider Society\Nusing the note they found.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.38,0:18:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it didn't go very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.34,0:18:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he ended up concluding that it was\Na just a hoax that was using the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.63,0:18:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.76,0:18:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.89,0:18:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On graduation day, one of the\Ngraduates said to Tanabe-{\i1}senpai{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.97,0:18:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I was the president of\Nthe Joro Spider Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.35,0:18:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give my regards to next\Nyear's president for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is, {\i1}if {\i0}you can ever find them."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.78,0:19:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they're recruiting\Nsomewhere for this year, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.61,0:19:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still haven't discovered\Nwhere, as of yet, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.87,0:19:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A single note...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.70,0:19:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Joro Spider Society...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.25,0:19:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.83,0:19:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.54,0:19:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you might say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.96,0:19:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I said you came\Nat just the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.34,0:19:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.59,0:19:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to go looking,\Nof course, for that note.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.93,0:19:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are 30 bulletin boards in all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.68,0:19:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That many? Are we going\Nto search them all?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.14,0:19:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.89,0:19:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quicker to think about\Nwhere it most likely might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.94,0:19:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.31,0:19:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What sort of place\Ndo you think it would be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.48,0:19:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.23,0:19:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I would post it on one of\Nthe school's corner bulletin boards,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.74,0:19:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where it would attract as\Nlittle attention as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.61,0:19:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's where you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.82,0:19:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.20,0:19:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposing that it's a recruitment note,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.54,0:19:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would be the 1st-floor\Nentrance bulletin board.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.54,0:19:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But that's where it would\Nstick out the most, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.62,0:19:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.00,0:19:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro apparently has something in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.42,0:20:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, looking at it like this,\NKamiyama High School is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.76,0:20:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. An Ink Painting\NClub, a Manga Research Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.39,0:20:06.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Rosy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.18,0:20:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a Go Club, a Basketball\NClub, a Track Club...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.89,0:20:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can barely see the\Nbulletin board itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.32,0:20:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.69,0:20:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm just being swamped\Nby the deluge of activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.03,0:20:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be an unfathomable world\Nto our energy-conserving Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.53,0:20:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, this is the first\Nbulletin board that new students see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.45,0:20:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it's a battleground area.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.54,0:20:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Battleground area? Oh, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.71,0:20:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this many things posted here,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.46,0:20:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an unauthorized bulletin wouldn't\Ndraw much attention, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.42,0:20:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.26,0:20:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As well? Is there some another reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah. Let's just start looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.10,0:20:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.85,0:20:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's the Global Action\NClub, the Debate Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.43,0:20:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and even a Hundred Poets Card Game Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.81,0:20:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Fortunetelling Club!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.06,0:20:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a friend who joined this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.44,0:20:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.61,0:21:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Koto Music Club,\Nthe Ping Pong Club, the Art Club...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.57,0:21:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... There doesn't seem to be\Na note from the Joro Spider Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.45,0:21:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.66,0:21:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure you'd be able to tell\Nwhat it is by looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.08,0:21:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.29,0:21:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to avoid the\NExecutive Committee's eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.96,0:21:16.42,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Baseball Club now seeking members
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.96,0:21:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there might be some kind of trick to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.29,0:21:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A trick, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.29,0:21:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if it {\i1}is {\i0}here, we'll find it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.46,0:21:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.17,0:21:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.85,0:21:29.60,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Joro Spider Society filling two vacancies
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it would be hidden\Nsomeplace less crowded.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.73,0:21:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a 1st-year mindset.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.94,0:21:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're as unpracticed as they are\Ntrying to be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.15,0:21:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this secret club had any sense,\Nthey'd be smarter than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.94,0:21:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true. Still, it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.78,0:21:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you say it, it seems\Nlike it should be so obvious,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.03,0:21:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and for some reason,\NI don't feel surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.79,0:21:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No approval stamp from\Nthe Executive Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.75,0:21:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time to do my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.08,0:22:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm going to turn my\Nessay in to the faculty room,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.46,0:22:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then head on home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.92,0:22:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, okay. I think I'll head home, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.47,0:22:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Well then,\NI guess this is goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.97,0:22:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"As unpracticed as they are\Ntrying to be different."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.18,0:22:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.77,0:22:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your "fight mystery with mystery"\Nplan was a real hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.49,0:22:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your help. For some reason,\NI had a feeling she was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.45,0:22:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm. So that's why you got\Nthat note and thumbtack ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.16,0:22:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, turns out you were\Nright on the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.79,0:22:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then again, Hotaro, why did you\Nset up that elaborate stunt
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.38,0:22:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just to change the subject\Noff of that piano mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.42,0:22:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it was because\Nyou weren't up to that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.59,0:22:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The music room was too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.55,0:22:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.80,0:22:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all. I just wanted to go\Nstraight to the entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.89,0:22:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,turn in my essay at the faculty room\Nnext to it, and then leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.98,0:23:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.19,0:23:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's you all right, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.94,0:23:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.44,0:23:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I have to do something, I do it quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.66,0:23:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, that won't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.20,0:23:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to announce your motto,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.04,0:23:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you should do it proudly,\Nwith your head held high.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.54,0:23:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounded to me just now like you\Nwere simply offering an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.51,0:23:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Intercepting a mystery\Nwith another mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.51,0:23:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, I like it. Nice curveball.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.72,0:23:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know what, Hotaro?\NIt wasn't your speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.18,0:23:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}showed up,\Nwhy didn't you just say "I don't know"?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.73,0:23:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the fundamental mistake\Nthat you made today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.28,0:23:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, that's the way\Nyou've always been, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.20,0:23:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.24,0:23:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"As unpracticed as you are\Ntrying to be different."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.58,0:23:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's exactly the way you were today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.41,0:24:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't at all used to\Nhaving Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}around.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.58,0:24:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you took such\Na roundabout detour.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.92,0:24:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might have been trying\Nto foil Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}today,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.76,0:24:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you know...\NI wasn't trying to foil her.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.72,0:24:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.47,0:24:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was just you putting the\Ncurrent state of affairs on hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.19,0:24:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On hold?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.77,0:24:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. On hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.82,0:24:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what do you think\Nthe whole music room deal is about?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.57,0:24:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.11,0:24:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "ghost" is supposed to have\Nmessed-up hair and bloodshot eyes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.20,0:24:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like someone just waking up?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.41,0:24:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.24,0:24:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Piano Club member was tired,\Nso she went to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.00,0:24:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To make sure she woke up before\Nthe school gates closed at 6:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.00,0:24:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she put "Moonlight Sonata"\Nin her CD player, and set the timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.25,0:24:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.51,0:24:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes sense. I'm sure if\Nyou'd gone there, you could tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.22,0:24:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The timer setting on the player\Nis probably still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.22,0:24:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The music room is too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.26,0:24:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I get it. But you know, Hotaro...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.06,0:25:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.72,0:25:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a hunch that going to the music room
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.64,0:25:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will end up having been the\Nenergy-conserving route, going forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.11,0:25:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's problems might end up\Ncosting you surprisingly dearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.86,0:25:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.70,0:25:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro! I don't plan to hold\Ntoday's events over you! Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.50,0:25:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On hold, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.05,0:25:38.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.01,0:25:41.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.77,0:25:45.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.77,0:25:51.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.25,0:26:11.30,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.09,0:26:22.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.52,0:26:29.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.02,0:26:34.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.40,0:26:40.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.12,0:26:45.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.08,0:26:48.17,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.17,0:26:51.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.88,0:26:55.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.88,0:27:01.14,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.14,0:27:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "The Prestigious\NClassic Lit Club's Activities."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.39,0:27:12.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Prestigious Classic Lit Club's Activities
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.68,0:27:14.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,
